# Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values.
**Never commit `.env` to version control.**

```env
# ─── Google Gemini API (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Leave blank to disable LLM watermark detection
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# ─── Server Bind Settings ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Defaults used if unset
HOST=0.0.0.0
PORT=7860
```

## Notes

- `GEMINI_API_KEY` — Obtain from [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/).
  When set, also flip `USE_GEMINI = True` in `Backend/config.py`.

- `HOST` / `PORT` — Override for deployment environments.
  Hugging Face Spaces auto-sets `PORT=7860`.

- All other tuneable settings (thresholds, weights, model names) live directly
  in `Backend/config.py` and are safe to commit.
